    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA85-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu talaivaṉ varavuṇarnta tōḻi talaivikku uraittatu (ET: talaimakaṭkuc colliyatu).</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what the condante, who had understood that HE would come, said to HER.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA85">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            āymalar maḻaikkaṇ ṭeṇpaṉi yuṟaippavum</l>
<l>            vēymaruḷ paṇaittōḷ viṟaliḻai nekiḻavu</l>
<l>            mampaṉ mūtū rarava māyiṉuṅ</l>
<l>            kuṟuvari yirumpuli yañcik kuṟunaṭaik</l>
<l>            kaṉṟuṭai vēḻa niṉṟukāt talku </l>
<l>            māriruḷ kaṭukiya vañcuvaru ciṟuneṟi</l>
<l>            vāraṟka tilla tōḻi cāraṟ</l>
<l>            kāṉava ṉeyta muḷavumāṉ koḻuṅkuṟai</l>
<l>            tēṅkamaḻ katuppiṟ koṭicci makiḻaṅkoṭuṅ</l>
<l>            kāntaḷañ ciṟukuṭip pakukku </l>
<l>            mōṅkumalai nāṭaṉiṉ ṉacaiyi ṉāṉē.</l>
        </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Even when clear dew drips from [your] rain eyes, choice flowers,</l>
<l>even when the victorious jewels on [your] bamboo-like bamboo shoulders become loose, even if the old village resounds in rumours,</l>
<l rend="indent3">please let him not come, friend,</l>
<l rend="indent">on the fearful small path he hastened in difficult darkness,</l>
<l rend="indent2">where the elephant bull remains on [his] guard, standing with</l>
<l rend="indent2">[his] calf of short steps, fearing the short-striped big tiger,</l>
<l>– in [his] yearning for you, the man from a land of high mountains,</l>
<l>were they distribute in the small hamlet of Malabar lilies,</l>
<l rend="indent2">that give delight to creeper-women with hair fragrant of honey,</l>
<l rend="indent2">the rich flesh of the male porcupine shot by the forest man.</l>
        </lg>
